Every Azure resource progresses through a lifecycle from creation to retirement. Managing this lifecycle efficiently reduces unnecessary costs and improves governance.

Typical lifecycle stages include:

* Planning
* Provisioning
* Configuration
* Monitoring
* Optimization
* Decommissioning

For example, temporary development resources should be removed after project completion instead of remaining active indefinitely.

A real-life use case is organizations periodically reviewing idle virtual machines and unused storage accounts to reduce cloud spending.

Managing the complete resource lifecycle improves operational efficiency and financial control.
